in%20the%20immediate%20aftermath%2C%20we%20would%20get%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%20%E2%80%94%20who%20would%20be%20the%20first%20female%20president%20and%20just%20its%20second%20Black%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usa.gov%2Fpresidential-succession%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclear%20presidential%20order%20of%20succession%3C%2Fa%3E%20outlined%20in%20the%20Constitution%20and%20the%20Presidential%20Succession%20Act%20of%201947%2C%20saying%20that%20if%20the%20president%20dies%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20takes%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20an%20electoral%20standpoint%2C%20Harris%20would%20also%20replace%20Biden%20as%20a%20Democratic%20presidential%20candidate.%20But%20his%20death%20would%20almost%20certainly%20open%20the%20door%20for%20other%20Democrats%20to%20jump%20into%20the%202024%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20national%20deadline%20to%20file%20to%20run%20for%20president%20of%20the%20United%20States.%20Instead%2C%20filing%20deadlines%20vary%20depending%20on%20the%20state%20and%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20states'%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fballotpedia.org%2FDeadline_to_run_for_president%2C_2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeadlines%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20already%20passed%2C%20however%2C%20meaning%20that%20state%20election%20officials%20would%20need%20to%20adjust%20them%20to%20allow%20new%20candidates%20to%20enter%20the%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20president%20died%20during%20primary%20season%20%E2%80%94%20which%20ends%20in%20mid-June%20%E2%80%94%20some%20states%20may%20postpone%20their%20scheduled%20primaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20some%20precedent%20for%20this%3B%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Farticle%2F2020-campaign-primary-calendar-coronavirus.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%20a%20dozen%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%20postponed%20their%20primaries%20or%20expanded%20vote-by-mail%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20a%20sitting%20president%20died%20after%20the%20primaries%20but%20before%20their%20party's%20convention%2C%20the%20other%20presidential%20candidates%20would%20have%20to%20make%20a%20case%20to%20every%20state%20delegation%20at%20the%20convention%20for%20why%20they%20should%20be%20the%20party's%20nominee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20if%20a%20president%20died%20after%20securing%20their%20party's%20nomination%20but%20before%20Election%20Day%2C%20both%20the%20Democratic%20and%20Republican%20parties%20have%20guidelines%20in%20place%20for%20selecting%20an%20alternate.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20both%20cases%2C%20the%20parties'%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprod-static.gop.com%2Fmedia%2FRules_Of_The_Republican_Party.pdf%3F_gl%3D1*14am007*_gcl_au*MTQ4Mzg0NzY1MC4xNjk0MDA5ODgy%26_ga%3D2.108222530.1599547227.1694009882-1687212181.1694009882%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erules%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdemocrats.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2FDNC-Charter-Bylaws-03.12.2022.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebylaws%3C%2Fa%3E%20state%20that%20they%20would%20have%20the%20power%20to%20vote%20on%20another%20nominee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-happens-if-president-dies-while-running-reelection%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700824981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bbe489c7d23cb3b9da153%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-happens-if-president-dies-while-running-reelection%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Joe%20Biden%20turned%2081%20on%20Monday%2C%20and%20it%20raises%20an%20obvious%20question%3A%20What%20happens%20if%20a%20sitting%20president%2