-Old%20Man's%20Intestines%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDoctors%20in%20the%20United%20States%20were%20left%20baffled%20after%20discovering%20a%20fully%20intact%20house%20fly%20inside%20a%20man's%20intestines%20during%20a%20colonoscopy.%20The%20finding%2C%20published%20in%20the%20American%20Journal%20of%20Gastroenterology%2C%20was%20made%20when%20a%2063-year-old%20man%20went%20in%20for%20a%20routine%20colon%20screening%20in%20Missouri.%20The%20colonoscopy%20was%20going%20normal%20until%20the%20doctors%20reached%20the%20transverse%20colon%20-%20the%20top%20of%20the%20large%20intestine%20-%20and%20came%20across%20a%20fully%20intact%20fly.%20%26quot%3BThis%20case%20represents%20a%20very%20rare%20colonoscopic%20finding%20and%20mystery%20on%20how%20the%20intact%20fly%20found%20its%20way%20to%20the%20transverse%20colon%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20doctors%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Missouri%20School%20of%20Medicine%20wrote%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.lww.com%2Fajg%2Fcitation%2F2023%2F10000%2Fto_be_a_fly_on_the_wall__a_mysterious_finding_on.7.aspx%5C%22%3Ejournal%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2063-year-old%20patient%2C%20whose%20identity%20hasn't%20been%20revealed%2C%20was%20equally%20bewildered%20by%20the%20discovery%20and%20had%20no%20idea%20how%20the%20insect%20got%20into%20his%20body.%20He%20told%20the%20doctors%20that%20he%20had%20only%20consumed%20clear%20liquids%20before%20his%20procedure%20and%2C%20two%20days%20before%2C%20had%20eaten%20pizza%20and%20lettuce%20-%20but%20could%20not%20recall%20a%20fly%20being%20on%20any%20of%20the%20food%20he%20ate.%20The%20man%20had%20no%20symptoms%20to%20suggest%20he%20had%20ingested%20it%2C%20doctors%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fly%20was%20not%20moving%20on%20its%20own%20or%20with%20manipulation%20with%20the%20scope%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20team%20wrote%20in%20the%20journal.%20Separately%2C%20speaking%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Famericas%2Fmissouri-man-live-fly-intestines-b2451725.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Independent%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Matthew%20Bechtold%2C%20the%20chief%20of%20Gastroenterology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Missouri%2C%20said%20that%20he%20and%20other%20doctors%20prodded%20the%20fly%20and%20confirmed%20it%20was%20dead.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fwhat-is-biohacking-the-wellness-trend-taking-internet-by-storm-4600361%5C%22%3EWhat%20Is%20Biohacking%3F%20The%20Wellness%20Trend%20Taking%20Internet%20By%20Storm%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Bechtold%20suggested%20a%20couple%20of%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20fly%20may%20have%20made%20its%20way%20to%20the%20man's%20stomach%20-%20through%20consumption%20or%20by%20entering%20his%20rectum%20-%20yet%20he%20and%20his%20fellow%20doctors%20remain%20unsure%20on%20how%20the%20house%20fly%20made%20its%20way%20into%20the%20transverse%20colon.%20Speaking%20to%20the%20outlet%2C%20Mr%20Bechtold%20said%20that%20if%20the%20fly%20had%20entered%20through%20the%20man's%20mouth%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20would%20think%20that%20upper%20digestive%20enzymes%20and%20stomach%20acid%20would%20have%20degraded%20the%20fly.%20However%2C%20the%20fly%20was%20intact%2C%20making%20this%20hypothesis%20less%20likely%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20from%20the%20bottom%2C%20an%20opening%20must%20have%20been%20created%20long%20enough%20for%20the%20fly%20to%20fly%20undetected%20into%20the%20colon%20and%20somehow%20make%20its%20way%20to%20the%20middle%20part%20of%20the%20colon%20with%20no%20light%20in%20a%20very%20curvy%2C%20large%20intestine.%20However%2C%20this%20seems%20unlikely%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Bechtold%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20been%20known%20in%20rare%20cases%20for%20flies%20and%20their%20larvae%20to%20infest%20the%20human%20intestines%20in%20a%20condition%20called%20intestinal%20myiasis.%20But%20people%20would%20have%20to%20have%20eaten%20food%20containing%20fly%20eggs%20and%20larvae%2C%20and%20rarely%20the%20eggs%20can%20survive%20stomach%20acid%20and%20hatch%2C%20then%20grow%20inside%20the%20body%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Library%20of%20Medicine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700812200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fh1avb29o_fly-inside-intestine_625x300_24_November_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fus-doctors-find-fully-intact-house-fly-inside-63-year-old-mans-intestines-4601996%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Doctors%20in%20the%20United%20States%20were%20left%20baffled%20after%20discovering%20a%20fully%20intact%20house%20fly%20inside%20a%20man's%20intestines%20during%20a%20colonoscopy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fus-doctors-find-fully-intact-house-fly-inside-63-year-old-mans-intestines-4601996%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fus-doctors-find-fully-intact-house-fly-inside-63-year-old-mans-intestines-4601996%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fus-doctors-find-fully-intact-house-fly-inside-63-year-old-mans-intestines-4601996%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20Ranbir%20moved%20from%20his%20chocolate%20boy%20avatar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700812091000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105468782%2Cimgsize-46494.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fanimal-to-raajneeti-times-when-ranbir-kapoor-moved-away-from-his-chocolate-boy-avatar%2Fphotostory%2F105468782.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105468782.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%