December%2016%2C%20prelude%20to%20his%20retirement%20on%20December%2025.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20November%2023%2C%20Thursday%2C%20the%20second%20day%20of%20the%20hearing%2C%20however%2C%20the%20bench%20understood%20the%20futility%20of%20hearing%20the%20case%2C%20with%20the%20Union%20government%20continuing%20to%20obstruct%20the%20hearing.%20Solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%2C%20who%20realised%20that%20he%20could%20not%20persuade%20the%20bench%20not%20to%20hear%20the%20case%2C%20sought%20more%20time%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20arguments%20of%20the%20petitioners%2C%20who%20he%20alleged%2C%20had%20%E2%80%9Cexpanded%20their%20challenge%20to%20the%202022%20verdict%20beyond%20the%20issues%20they%20had%20initially%20raised%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Wednesday%20and%20Thursday%2C%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20senior%20counsel%2C%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20made%20detailed%20submissions%20before%20the%20bench%2C%20which%20in%20retrospect%2C%20seemed%20to%20be%20in%20vain.%20Senior%20counsel%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%2C%20who%20made%20submissions%20on%20behalf%20of%20another%20petitioner%20Sanjay%20Chabbaria%20on%20Thursday%2C%20vehemently%20protested%20against%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20plea%20for%20more%20time%20to%20respond%2C%20saying%20the%20petitioners%20had%20not%20raised%20any%20new%20points%2C%20and%20were%20not%20pressing%20their%20amendments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENotwithstanding%20the%20waste%20of%20judicial%20time%2C%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20plea%20landed%20the%20bench%20in%20a%20quandary.%20Justice%20Kaul%20pleaded%20helplessness%2C%20by%20saying%20he%20was%20adjourning%20the%20hearing%2C%20and%20placing%20the%20case%20before%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20for%20constituting%20a%20new%20bench%20to%20hear%20it%2C%20in%20view%20of%20his%20impending%20retirement.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20doing%20this%20with%20a%20little%20heavy%20heart%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20while%20dictating%20the%20order.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20response%20to%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20plea%20for%20more%20time%20to%20respond%20to%20new%20points%20in%20the%20amended%20petition%2C%20Justice%20Kaul%20said%20tongue-in-cheek%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20know%20everything.%20But%20sometimes%2C%20things%20must%20be%20left%20unsaid.%E2%80%9D%20He%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9COn%20this%20side%2C%20we%20see%20and%20hear%20many%20things%2C%20but%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20say%20many%20things.%20On%20a%20lighter%20note%2C%20I%20will%20have%20that%20privilege%20from%20January%201.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackground%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20case%20before%20the%20special%20bench%20sought%20a%20reference%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20previous%20decision%20in%20%3Cem%3EVijay%20Madanlal%20Choudhary%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022)%20to%20a%20larger%20bench.%20The%202022%20judgment%20was%20rendered%20by%20a%20three-judge%20bench%20comprising%20Justices%20A.M.%20Khanwilkar%2C%20Dinesh%20Maheshwari%20and%20C.T.%20Ravi%20Kumar.%20The%20judgment%2C%20authored%20by%20Justice%20Khanwilkar%20two%20days%20before%20his%20retirement%2C%20upheld%20the%20wide%20powers%20of%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Enforcement%20(ED)%20to%20issue%20summons%2C%20record%20statements%2C%20make%20arrests%20and%20search%20and%20seize%20property.%20It%20was%20also%20held%20that%20the%20Act%2C%20which%20imposes%20its%20own%20bail%20conditions%2C%20is%20not%20a%20penal%20law.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMehta%20opposed%20the%20hearing%20by%20the%20special%20bench%20%E2%80%93%20also%20comprising%20three%20judges%20%E2%80%93%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20reconsideration%20of%20a%20coordinate%20bench%20decision%20was%20an%20%E2%80%98abuse%20of%20the%20process%20of%20law%E2%80%99.%20Mehta%20also%20opposed%20it%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20a%20review%20petition%20against%20the%202022%20judgment%20was%20pending%20before%20the%20court.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Justice%20Kaul-led%20bench%2C%20however%2C%20rejected%20the%20contention%20by%20relying%20on%20precedents%20to%20justify%20the%20reconsideration%20of%20a%20judgment%20by%20a%20coordinate%20bench%20of%20similar%20strength.%C2%A0%20The%20bench%20reserved%20its%20right%20to%20consider%20whether%20the%20case%20should%20be%20referred%20to%20a%20larger%20bench.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20Sibal%20contended%20before%20the%20bench%20that%20the%202022%20judgment%20erroneously%20upheld%20provisions%20which%20breached%20personal%20liberty%20under%20Article%2021.%20On%20Thursday%2C%20Singhvi%20sought%20to%20substantiate%20that%20amendments%20to%20Section%2045%20of%20the%20PMLA%20%E2%80%93%20relating%20to%20cognisable%20and%20non-bailable%20offences%20%E2%80%93%20were%20wrongfully%20upheld%20in%20the%202022%20judgment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20composition%20of%20the%20new%20bench%2C%20to%20be%20constituted%20by%20the%20CJI%2C%20to%20hear%20the%20case%2C%20will%20indicate%20whether%20the%20case%20will%20at%20all%20be%20heard%20by%20a%20larger%20bench.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700809201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F12%2F09153755%2Fsanjay-kaul.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Freconsidering-pmla-judgment-justice-kaul-abandon-hearing-centre-more-time%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%20sought%20more%20time%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20arguments%2C%20Justice%20S.K.%20Kaul%2C%20who%20will%20retire%20on%20December%2025%2C%20had%20no%20option%20but%20to%20discontinue%20further%20hearing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Freconsidering-pmla-judgment-justice-kaul-abandon-hearing-centre-more-time%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22