0the%20'Unknown%20Pneumonia'%20Outbreak%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24092504%2F6838768118_4231c20017_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Amid%20an%20ongoing%20and%20fresh%20outbreak%20of%20what%20has%20emerged%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunknown%20pneumonia%E2%80%9D%20in%20China%20leading%20to%20crowding%20at%20healthcare%20facilities%20in%20northern%20China%2C%20the%20government%20of%20the%20country%20has%20ruled%20out%20the%20presence%20of%20any%20new%20or%20unknown%20pathogen.%20This%2C%20at%20least%20as%20of%20now%2C%20should%20put%20to%20rest%20fears%20of%20a%20bigger%20outbreak%20which%20could%20have%20pandemic%20potential.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EQuoting%20official%20conversation%20with%20Chinese%20health%20authorities%20from%20the%20Chinese%20Center%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%2C%20and%20the%20Beijing%20Children%E2%80%99s%20Hospital%2C%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%20said%20on%20November%2023%20that%20the%20upsurge%20in%20hospital%20admissions%20of%20children%20were%20due%20to%20Mycoplasma%20Pneumoniae%20%E2%80%93%20a%20bacterial%20infection%20%E2%80%93%20from%20May%3B%20and%20Respiratory%20Syncytial%20Virus%20(RSV)%2C%20adenovirus%20and%20influenza%20%E2%80%93%20all%20viral%20infections%20%E2%80%93%20from%20October%20this%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20these%20bacterial%20and%20viral%20infections%20are%20well%20known%20and%20treatments%20to%20these%20are%20available%20%E2%80%93%20unlike%20in%20case%20of%20a%20novel%20pathogen%20(a%20virus%20or%20bacteria).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20recent%20outbreak%20in%20China%20brought%20back%20eerie%20memories%20of%20the%20Sars-Cov-2%20(novel%20coronavirus)%20outbreak.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20also%20described%20as%20pneumonia%20of%20%E2%80%9Cunknown%20aetiology%20(unknown%20cause)%E2%80%9D%20in%20one%20of%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Femergencies%2Fdisease-outbreak-news%2Fitem%2F2020-DON229%23%3A~%3Atext%3DDescription%2520of%2520the%2520Situation%2CCity%252C%2520Hubei%2520Province%2520of%2520China.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20first%20statements%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20the%20WHO%20that%20was%20published%20after%20the%20outbreak%20of%20COVID-19.%20But%20now%2C%20the%20role%20of%20any%20unknown%20pathogen%20has%20been%20ruled%20out%2C%20at%20least%2C%20for%20the%20time%20being%2C%20while%20accepting%20the%20surge%20in%20cases.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%5BThe%5D%20Chinese%20authorities%20advised%20that%20there%20has%20been%20no%20detection%20of%20any%20unusual%20or%20novel%20pathogens%20or%20unusual%20clinical%20presentations%2C%20including%20in%20Beijing%20and%20Liaoning%2C%20but%20only%20the%20aforementioned%20general%20increase%20in%20respiratory%20illnesses%20due%20to%20multiple%20known%20pathogens%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20WHO%20has%20said%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20November%2022%2C%20a%20day%20earlier%2C%20the%20WHO%20made%20its%20first%20formal%20statement%20regarding%20the%20outbreak%20in%20China.%20Various%20images%20circulated%20on%20social%20media%20in%20which%20hospitals%2C%20especially%20treating%20children%2C%20were%20shown%20to%20be%20overwhelmed.%20In%20the%20November%2022%20statement%2C%20the%20WHO%20had%20said%20it%20had%20sought%20more%20information%20from%20China.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WHO%20move%20was%20necessitated%20by%20a%20report%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpromedmail.org%2Fpromed-post%2F%3Fplace%3D8713261%2C353%23promedmailmap%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EProMed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20November%2021%20which%20spoke%20of%20undiagnosed%20pneumonia%20epidemics%20going%20on%20in%20China.%20ProMed%20is%20an%20international%20forum%20that%20identifies%20infectious%20diseases%20outbreaks%20globally%2C%20and%20is%20usually%20the%20first%20platform%20to%20alert%20the%20global%20scientific%20community%20about%20them%20%E2%80%93%20as%20it%20did%20for%20Covid-19.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20the%20outbreak%20of%20pneumonia%20in%20China%2C%20children%E2%80%99s%20hospitals%20in%20Beijing%2C%20Liaoning%20and%20other%20places%20were%20overwhelmed%20with%20sick%20children%2C%20and%20schools%20and%20classes%20were%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20suspension%2C%E2%80%9D%20ProMed%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WHO%20wanted%20to%20know%20whether%20there%20were%20%E2%80%9Cclusters%E2%80%9D%20of%20%E2%80%9Cundiagnosed%20pneumonia%E2%80%9D%20in%20Beijing%20and%20Liaoning%20and%20if%20the%20current%20outbreak%20was%20a%20general%20pattern%20of%20increase%20in%20respiratory%20illnesses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Could%20be%20RSV%20or%20HMPV%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20spoke%20to%20three%20experts%20and%20all%20of%20them%2C%20by%20and%20large%2C%20made%20observations%20similar%20to%20the%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20latest%20statement%20on%20the%20current%20outbreak.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20there%20are%20children%20%5Bwho%20are%20mostly%20infected%5D%2C%20it%20could%20be%20RSV%20or%20Human%20Metapneumovirus%20(HMPV)%20%E2%80%93%20both%20known%20to%20cause%20respiratory%20illness%20in%20children%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Shahid%20Jameel%2C%20a%20virologist.%20Jameel%20is%20currently%20a%20research%20fellow%20at%20the%20Oxford%20University%E2%80%99s%20Green%20Templeton%20College.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERSV%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20(US-CDC)%20is%20a%20common%20viral%20respiratory%20infection%20that%20usually%20causes%20mild%2C%20cold-like%20symptoms%20and%20people%20can%20recover%20in%20a%20week%20with%20or%20without%20use%20of%20antibiotics.%20However%2C%20some%20serious%20cases%20may%20require%20hospitalisation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20Mycoplasma%20Pneumonia%20is%20a%20bacterial%20respiratory%20system%20which%20is%20usually%20considered%20mild%20but%20serious%20cases%20be%20hospitalised.%20Both%20of%20them%20are%20transmitted%20through%20droplets%20of%20an%20infected%20person%20or%20a%20close%20contact%20with%20her.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20have%20been%20RSV%20outbreaks%20elsewhere%20%5Balso%20apart%20from%20China%20%5Dafter%20good%20years%20due%20to%20quarantine%20and%20other%20restrictions%20%5Bbeing%20lifted%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jameel%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WHO%20also%20said%20something%20similar.%20%E2%80%9CSome%20of%20these%20increases%20are%20earlier%20in%20the%20season%20than%20historically%20experienced%2C%20but%20not%20unexpected%20given%20the%20lifting%20of%20COVID-19%20restrictions%2C%20as%20similarly%20experienced%20in%20other%20countries%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20explained.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmesh%20Adalja%2C%20a%20senior%20scholar%20at%20Johns%20Hopkins%20Center%20for%20Health%20Security%2C%20says%20the%20current%20outbreak%20in%20China%20seemed%20to%20mimic%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20US%20earlier.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20appears%20that%20this%20outbreak%20is%20likely%20the%20result%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eseveral%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20known%20respiratory%20pathogens%2C%20including%20Mycoplasma%20Pneumoniae%2C%20all%20attacking%20at%20once%20%E2%80%94%20similar%20to%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20US%20last%20year%20with%20simultaneous%20outbreaks%20of%20RSV%2C%20influenza%2C%20and%20COVID-19%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20response%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20now%3F%20Why%20China%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncidentally%2C%20China%20had%20followed%20what%20was%20called%20%E2%80%98Zero%20Covid%E2%80%99%20policy.%20It%20locked%20up%2C%20as%20per%20stringent%20measures%20of%20lockdown%20for%20COVID-19%2C%20large%20swathes%20of%20the%20population%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time%20%E2%80%93%20longer%20than%20many%20other%20countries.%20This%20resulted%20in%20a%20scenario%20in%20which%20the%20population%20didn%E2%80%99t%20get%20exposed%20to%20other%20respiratory%20viruses%20or%20bacteria%20also%2C%20in%20the%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0And%2C%20once%20the%20measures%20were%20lifted%20this%20winter%2C%C2%A0%20this%20population%20got%20exposed%20to%20all%20of%20them%20leading%20to%20the%20surge%20in%20cases.%20Moreover%2C%20not%20getting%20exposed%20to%20these%20pathogens%20for%20a%20long%20time%20could%20also%20have%20created%20what%20is%20known%20as%20%E2%80%98immunological%20deficit%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20a%20deficiency%20in%20natural%20immunity%20acquired%20against%20the%20pathogens%20due%20to%20exposure%20to%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBharat%20Pankhania%2C%20an%20infectious%20diseases%20expert%20with%20University%20of%20Exter%20Medical%20School%2C%20UK%2C%20believes%20the%20%E2%80%98deficit%E2%80%99%20might%20not%20provide%20the%20complete%20answer%20to%20the%20ongoing%20outbreak.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CImmunological%20deficit%20is%20not%20surprising%E2%80%A6but%20then%20you%20can%20have%20more%20people%20infected%20than%20expected%20because%20of%20circumstances%20like%20crowded%20schools%2C%20crowded%20shops%2C%20buses%2C%20trains%E2%80%A6and%20there%20is%20winter%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20difficult%20to%20disentangle%20%5Bwhether%5D%20it%20is%20an%20immunological%20deficit%2C%20or%20is%20it%20environmental%20circumstances.%20Or%20perhaps%20both%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENonetheless%2C%20Pankhania%20stressed%20that%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20patients%20responding%20to%20the%20drugs%20in%20this%20outbreak%20is%20a%20pointer%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20is%20not%20an%20unknown%20infection.%20The%20Chinese%20authorities%2C%20per%20WHO%2C%20have%20also%20said%20there%20is%20no%20change%20in%20the%20presentation%20of%20these%20diseases%20vis-a-vis%20the%20patterns%20already%20known.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20next%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECurrently%2C%20going%20by%20the%20data%20provided%20by%20the%20Chinese%20authorities%2C%20the%20WHO%20has%20assessed%20that%20the%20outbreak%20of%20the%20respiratory%20illnesses%20are%20caused%20by%20the%20known%20pathogens%20which%20are%20readily%20treatable%20with%20antibiotics%2C%20if%20needed.%20And%2C%20therefore%2C%20there%20was%20no%20cause%20of%20immediate%20alarm.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20Pankhania%20and%20Adalja%20said%20the%20Chinese%20authorities%20must%20share%20data%20with%20the%20global%20scientific%20community.%20They%20must%C2%A0%20publish%20the%20detailed%20findings%20of%20their%20inquiry%20besides%20sharing%20genome%20sequences%20of%20the%20samples%20tested.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WHO%20has%20also%20added%20though%20information%20available%20is%20%E2%80%9Climited%E2%80%9D%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfully%20characterise%E2%80%9D%20the%20overall%20risk%20even%20though%20winter%20season%20is%20known%20to%20create%20a%20spike%20in%20respiratory%20infections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20sounding%20a%20cautionary%20note%2C%20it%20said%20it%20will%20continue%20to%20closely%20monitor%20the%20situation%20and%20would%20be%20in%20close%20contact%20with%20national%20authorities%20of%20China.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700798192000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24092504%2F6838768118_4231c20017_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fchina-pneumonia-outbreak-who-pandemic%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chinese%C2%A0authorities%20told%20the%20WHO%20that%20the%20current%20outbreak%20is%C2%A0related%20to%20'already%20known'%20viruses%20or%20bacteria%2C%20thus%20ruling%20out%20any%20potential%20pandemic.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fchina-pneumonia-outbreak-who-pandemic%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tesla%20may%20invest%20%242%20billion%20for%20manufacturing%20in%20India%20but%20with%20conditions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700797232000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-11%2F22%2Ffull%2F1700631619-6093.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fauto%2Ftesla-may-invest-2-billion-for-manufacturing-in-india-but-with-conditions-123112400120_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tesla%20is%20also%20likely%20to%20commit%2020%25%20localisation%20in%20its%20Made%20in%20India%20cars%20in%20the%20first%20two%20years%20and%20it%20may%20increase%20to%2040%25%20in%20four%20years%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fauto%2Ftesla-may-invest-2-billion-for-manufacturing-in-india-but-with-conditions-123112400120_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findustry%2Fauto%2Ftesla-may-invest-2-billion-for-manufacturing-in-india-but-with-conditions-123112400120_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fi