e%20satellite%20in%20orbit%20had%20failed.%20For%20North%20Korea%2C%20this%20is%20a%20much-desired%20success.%20The%20earlier%20attempts%20had%20taken%20place%20during%20May%20and%20August.%20The%20way%20North%20Korea%20handled%20these%20recent%20failures%20and%20continued%20to%20work%20towards%20success%20indicates%20maturity%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20scientific%20and%20political%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20North%20Korean%20state%20was%20unusually%20honest%20in%20accepting%20its%20recent%20failures.%20No%20false%20claims%20about%20the%20success%20were%20made%2C%20and%20neither%20was%20the%20world%20kept%20in%20the%20dark%20to%20guess%20about%20its%20intentions.%20There%20were%20no%20attempts%20of%20any%20false%20self-glorification.%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20may%20have%20realised%20that%20the%20process%20of%20technology%20development%20is%20difficult%20and%20requires%20patience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20appears%20to%20have%20understood%20that%20to%20leap%20into%20the%20space%20domain%2C%20outside%20assistance%20is%20required.%20Between%20September%2012%20and%2017%2C%20Kim%20made%20an%20official%20visit%20to%20Russia.%20One%20of%20the%20meetings%20between%20him%20and%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20was%20at%20the%20Vostochny%20Cosmodrome%2C%20a%20Russian%20spaceport.%20There%20is%20both%20symbolic%20and%20strategic%20significance%20to%20the%20selection%20of%20the%20location%20and%20leads%20one%20to%20ask%20if%20the%20recent%20spy%20satellite%20success%20was%20assisted%20by%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F23184147%2FKim_Jong-un_and_Vladimir_Putin_2023-09-13_01.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F23184147%2FKim_Jong-un_and_Vladimir_Putin_2023-09-13_01.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F23184147%2FKim_Jong-un_and_Vladimir_Putin_2023-09-13_01-300x153.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686137%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22522%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EKim%20Jong-un%20and%20Vladimir%20Putin%20before%20visiting%20the%20Vostochny%20Cosmodrome.%20Photo%3A%20Kremlin.ru%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHistory%20of%20North%20Korea%E2%80%99s%20space%20programme%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20long%20time%2C%20North%20Korea%2C%20along%20with%20Iran%2C%20have%20been%20accused%20of%20using%20their%20space%20programmes%20for%20signalling%20their%20missile%20capabilities.%20However%2C%20the%20way%20in%20which%20North%20Korea%20has%20been%20undertaking%20missile%20testing%20during%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20it%20is%20obvious%20that%20it%20does%20not%20require%20any%20such%20smokescreen.%20Today%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20judge%20the%20North%20Korean%20space%20programme%20on%20its%20merit%20and%20the%20actual%20rationale%20behind%20such%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20September%204%2C%201998%2C%20the%20North%20Korean%20authorities%20claimed%20the%20successful%20launch%20of%20their%20first%20artificial%20satellite%2C%20Kwangmyongsong-1%20(Brightstar-1).%20Experts%2C%20at%20that%20time%2C%20had%20opined%20that%20the%20mission%20was%20not%20a%20success.%20North%20Korea%20is%20known%20to%20have%20achieved%20success%20in%20putting%20the%20satellite%20into%20orbit%20in%20its%20fourth%20attempt%20on%20December%201%2C%202012%2C%20and%20this%20success%20earned%20it%20the%20tag%20of%20spacefaring%20state.%20In%202016%2C%20North%20Korea%20successfully%20launched%20Kwangmyongsong-4%20into%20the%20Low%20Earth%20Orbit%20or%20LEO%20(payload%20could%20be%20around%20200%20kg).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Democratic%20People%E2%80%99s%20Republic%20of%20Korea%20(DPRK)%E2%80%99s%20space%20programme%20could%20be%20viewed%20as%20an%20expansion%20of%20its%20missile%20programme.%20The%20Korean%20Committee%20of%20Space%20Technology%20(KCST)%20was%20established%20sometime%20during%20the%201980s.%20This%20agency%20was%20responsible%20for%20research%2C%20satellite%20manufacture%20and%20launching%2C%20and%20managing%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20rocket%20launch%20sites.%20Subsequently%2C%20on%20April%201%2C%202013%2C%20the%20National%20Aerospace%20Development%20Administration%20(NADA)%20was%20established%2C%20which%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20DPRK%E2%80%99s%20central%20institution%20to%20organise%20all%20space%20development%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20time%20now%2C%20North%20Korea%20has%20been%20focusing%20its%20efforts%20on%20expanding%20in%20the%20space%20domain%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20military-relevant%20applications.%20In%202017%2C%20it%20announced%20a%20five-year%20plan%20to%20conquer%20space.%20As%20per%20this%2C%20it%20had%20a%20plan%20in%20place%20for%20building%20a%20satellite%20communication%20system%20by%20June%202019.%20However%2C%20this%20has%20not%20happened%20so%20far%20and%20nothing%20much%20is%20known%20in%20this%20regard.%20During%20a%20party%20congress%20(January%202021)%2C%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20mentioned%20the%20proposal%20for%20developing%20military%20reconnaissance%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2031%2C%20North%20Korea%E2%80%99s%20first%20attempt%20to%20put%20its%20first%20spy%20satellite%20into%20space%20failed.%20This%20mission%20involved%20the%20launching%20of%20the%20Malligyong-1%20satellite%20by%20using%20the%20newly%20developed%20Chollima-1%20rocket.%20As%20per%20North%20Korea%E2%80%99s%20news%20agency%2C%20the%20failure%20resulted%20from%20the%20low%20reliability%20of%20the%20new%20engine%20system%20used%20on%20the%20Chollima-1%20rocket%20and%20the%20unstable%20character%20of%20the%20fuel.%20The%20second%20launch%20undertaken%20on%20August%2024%20failed%20during%20the%20third%20stage%20of%20its%20flight.%20The%20state%20agency%20was%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20the%20failure%20was%20due%20to%20an%20error%20in%20the%20emergency%20blasting%20system%20during%20the%20third-stage%20flight%20and%20the%20issue%20was%20rectifiable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImplications%20for%20the%20world%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Korea%20is%20a%20nuclear%20weapon%20state.%20It%20is%20advocating%20its%20nuclear%20and%20missile%20programmes%20as%20formidable%20pillars%20of%20its%20security%20architecture.%20Now%20space%20is%20emerging%20as%20a%20new%20pillar%20in%20this%20structure.%20Having%20operational%20spy%20satellites%20directly%20or%20indirectly%20improves%20the%20%E2%80%98worth%E2%80%99%20of%20DPRK%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20deterrence%20mechanism.%20Pyongyang%20is%20open%20about%20its%20space%20ambitions%20and%20argues%20that%20it%20has%20a%20%E2%80%98sovereign%20right%E2%80%99%20to%20develop%20spy%20satellites%20to%20address%20its%20security%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20the%20United%20States%20and%20South%20Korean%20administrations%20are%20not%20found%20working%20towards%20any%20possible%20inter-Korean%20rapprochement.%20Together%20with%20Japan%2C%20they%20condemned%20the%20launch%2C%20which%2C%20according%20to%20them%2C%20used%20ballistic%20missile%20technology%20in%20violation%20of%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%20resolutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20high%20time%20for%20them%20to%20realise%20that%20old%20ideas%20of%20sanctions%2C%20arms%2C%20and%20export%20control%20measures%20and%20undertaking%20military%20exercises%20in%20Korean%20waters%20actually%20mean%20nothing%20to%20a%20state%20like%20North%20Korea%2C%20which%20is%20so%20brazen%20in%20its%20approach.%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20understands%20what%20such%20powers%20have%20done%20to%20Colonel%20Gaddafi%20and%20Saddam%20Hussein.%20He%20is%20not%20keen%20on%20any%20reconciliation%20from%20the%20position%20of%20weakness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkraine%20war%20and%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20increasing%20military%20needs%20for%20artillery%20shells%20and%20other%20munitions%20are%20drawing%20North%20Korea%20closer%20to%20Russia.%20In%20future%2C%20Russia-DPRK-China%20nexus%20is%20likely%20to%20emerge%20as%20a%20major%20nuisance%20for%20the%20US.%20It%20is%20important%20for%20the%20US%20to%20realise%20that%20taking%20a%20maximalist%20position%20against%20North%20Korea%20(that%20they%20should%20denuclearise)%20is%20not%20going%20to%20help.%C2%A0They%20need%20to%20start%20a%20process%20of%20constructive%20engagement.%20Possibly%2C%20space%20technologies%20could%20be%20a%20%E2%80%98low-hanging%20fruit%E2%80%99%20in%20this%20regard.%20These%20technologies%20are%20dual-use%20technologies%20with%20significant%20civilian%20utility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20North%20Korea%20needs%20greater%20assistance%20for%20socioeconomic%20development.%20Could%20the%20US%20think%20of%20using%20space%20technologies%20as%20an%20option%20in%20this%20regard%3F%20Some%20%E2%80%98outside%20the%20box%E2%80%99%20thinking%20is%20required%20to%20address%20the%20North%20Korean%20conundrums.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAjey%20Lele%20researches%20space%20issues%20and%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EInstitutions%20That%20Shaped%20Modern%20India%3A%20ISRO%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700793026000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F23184734%2FScreenshot-2023-11-23-at-6.45.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Fcontext-concerns-north-koreas-spy-satellite-launch%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20and%20Japan%20condemned%20the%20launch%2C%20accusing%20Pyongyang%20of%20using%20ballistic%20missile%20technology%20in%20violation%20of%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%20resolutions.%20Can%20such%20a%20maximalist%20position%20against%20North%20Kor